title: South Korea Reiterates Interest in Trans-Pacific Partnership
text:
SEOUL—South Korea reiterated its interest in joining the Trans-Pacific Partnership, indicating that the Asian-Pacific trading bloc has the potential to grow beyond its initial 12 members after a deal was struck to lower trade barriers between the founding nations Monday.
